    authors: ["Christian E. Posta", "Rinor Maloku"],
    description: "Many enterprise applications intertwine code that defines an app’s behavior with code that defines its network communication and other non-functional concerns. The “service mesh” pattern, implemented by platforms like Istio, helps you push operational issues into the infrastructure so the application code is easier to understand, maintain, and adapt.  teaches you how to implement a full-featured Istio-based service mesh to manage a microservices application. With the skills you learn in this comprehensive tutorial, you’ll be able to delegate the complex infrastructure of your cloud-native applications to Istio!",
