  %{
    authors: ["Paul Orl"],
    description: "To score a job in data science, machine learning, computer graphics, and cryptography, you need to bring strong math skills to the party.  teaches the math you need for these hot careers, concentrating on what you need to know as a developer. Filled with lots of helpful graphics and more than 200 exercises and mini-projects, this book unlocks the door to interesting–and lucrative!–careers in some of today’s hottest programming fields.",
    price: "$29.99",
    title: "Math for Programmers"
