    authors: ["Bruce A. Tate"],
    description: "It is a well-known fact that most software projects fail. Drawing important lessons from common failures is the goal of .Reusing design patterns is not enough for success: patterns are like partial maps of dangerous terrain. They help, but don't prevent you from getting lost.  teaches you how to recognize when you are lost, and how to get back on the right path. It illustrates common pitfalls of Java programming through code examples; it then refactors the code and explains why the new solutions are safe.",
